# Floating Button Behavior

Normal state:

The button appears as a circle.

When pressed:

- nothing special happens

When long pressed:

The circle should transform into a radial volume controller.

The animation should feel smooth.

The UI should expand naturally from the existing button.

---

# Volume Control Interaction

While long pressing:

A circular slider appears.

The user should move vertically.

Moving upward:

- increases volume

Moving downward:

- decreases volume

The UI should visualize the current volume using a circular progress indicator similar to:

- pie chart
- radial progress
- circular arc

The filled arc should animate in real time.

When the finger is released:

- the radial control smoothly collapses
- the button returns to its original appearance

The transition should feel premium.

